# Real-Time Order Sync Walkthrough

I have completed the integration of real-time order synchronization between the **User Mobile App** and the **Rider Mobile App**. This ensures a seamless delivery experience from the moment an order is placed until it reaches the customer's doorstep.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Backend Infrastructure 🏗️
- **WebSocket Gateway:** Enhanced [OrdersGateway](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/backend-api/src/orders/orders.gateway.ts#10-53) with a dedicated `riders_room`.
- **Broadcasting:** Implemented automatic order broadcasting to all online riders upon checkout.
- **Rider Assignment:** Created `POST /orders/:id/accept` to safely assign a rider to a pending order and notify the customer.
- **Status Management:** Added granular status tracking (`confirmed`, `preparing`, `out_for_delivery`, `delivered`) with real-time customer notifications.

### 2. Rider App Features 🚴
- **Real-Time Dashboard:** Riders now see a live list of pending orders within their zone.
- **WebSocket Integration:** Riders receive instant alerts when a new order is placed.
- **Order Acceptance:** A single tap accepts an order, navigates to the store, and updates the customer.
- **Delivery Lifecycle:** Full support for updating order status from "Arrived at Store" to "Delivered".

### 3. User App Tracking 📱
- **Live Updates:** The [OrderTrackingScreen](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/src/screens/OrderTrackingScreen.tsx#19-210) remains synced with the rider's progress via WebSockets.
- **Rider Details:** Customers now see their assigned rider's name and can call them directly from the tracking screen.

